# NAVYK General Rules

## Mission
NAVYK is a Career OS for students. Every feature must help users progress toward career outcomes.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode. NO `any`. NO `@ts-ignore` without explanation.
- All public functions must have JSDoc with description and parameters.
- Use discriminated unions for statuses (CareerStatus, ApplicationStatus).
- Always type API responses via shared types from `@navyk/types`.

## Naming
- Component files: PascalCase (UserDashboard.tsx)
- Utility files: camelCase (formatDate.ts)
- API routes: kebab-case (/career-roadmap)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE
- Variables/functions: camelCase
- Interfaces: PascalCase, NO I-prefix (User not IUser)
- Enums: PascalCase (ApplicationStatus, UserRole)

## Commits (Conventional Commits)
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- refactor: refactoring
- docs: documentation
- test: tests
- chore: config, dependencies

## Forbidden
- Hardcoded strings in Russian/Kazakh in code — use i18n keys only
- Magic numbers without named constants
- Direct DB queries from frontend — API only
- Secrets in code — .env only
- Mutating props or state directly
